      <description>&lt;div&gt; I am concerned about the long term viability of the everquest virtual world.&lt;br&gt;We are used to seeing unintended changes with every expansion, and the inevitable&lt;br&gt;&amp;quot;patch to fix the patch&amp;quot;.  What worries me is that the fundamental playability of&lt;br&gt;the game will become so fragile that future expansions will be impossible.  I began&lt;br&gt;playing in 2003.  With the exception of the DX9 patch, it seems to me that major&lt;br&gt;changes in the game produced an escalating number of bugs as time passed.  I would&lt;br&gt;appreciate the comments of others on their perceptions of this apparent trend. &lt;br&gt;Also any progammers that have insight into keeping an old software growing and&lt;br&gt;functional please contribute.        &lt;/div&gt;</description>
